254
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:43,370
At 7:30 pm, Terafune was arrested on suspicion of hitting on someone.

255
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,440
Hey, get off!

256
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,370
I'll go! Let go of me!

257
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:44,270
Crap.

258
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:45,390
We will now begin the interrogation.

259
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:46,290
Cut it out!

260
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:49,050
Huh... Didn't know that about Terafune-kun.

261
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:50,270
Sorry, Akari.

262
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:54,060
We said we'd create a chance for you, and things turned out like this.

263
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:58,020
It's okay. Thanks. I'm grateful to all of you.

264
00:11:58,020 --> 00:12:04,160
Delicious Chocolate Banana Deluxe

265
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:01,400
Let's ask the boys to get us something sweet, too!

266
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:04,160
Yeah. We should go after them. Wait here a sec.

267
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,810
Okay.

268
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,910
I wore a yukata because Minami-kun was coming.

269
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:13,750
I put a lot of effort into my makeup,

270
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:16,540
and I spent more time than usual on my hair.

271
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:20,720
I thought this would be my chance.

272
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:24,260
I thought if I saw Minami-kun here, something would change.

273
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:30,020
So why did I feel relieved when I heard Minami-kun couldn't make it?

274
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,100
I love Minami-kun.

275
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,730
Chasing after Minami-kun like I used to...

276
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:40,860
Simply acting out the role of Jiro's wife like I used to...

277
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:44,240
But... things changing to be like that is still...

278
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,870
It's still scary to me.

279
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:51,040
I know I'm not the one next to either of them.

280
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:53,120
Once I make a choice, I'll never again...

281
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,910
Terafune, just give up already.

282
00:12:57,910 --> 00:13:00,670
No! Watanabe said she likes fish.

283
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:03,130
Pretty sure she meant she likes to eat fish.

284
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:07,130
No, no! Why am I getting all discouraged now?

285
00:13:07,130 --> 00:13:09,890
Everyone's cheering me on! I have to do my best!

286
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:12,430
I know! I could stop by where he works!

287
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:13,890
Wow, look!

288
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:15,740
Hey, he's pretty hot!

289
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:17,060
Do you think he's famous?

290
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:19,150
But the girl with him seems like his girlfriend.

291
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:23,430
Minami-kun...

292
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:25,030
He said he was working...

293
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:34,790
Maybe it's time to bow out gracefully and give up.

294
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:37,360
But why?

295
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:39,100
I've tried so hard.

296
00:13:44,570 --> 00:13:45,990
We're back, Akari!

297
00:13:45,990 --> 00:13:48,300
We've got fresh baby castella cakes!

298
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:51,740
What's wrong? You look a little pale.

299
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:54,560
Do I? Sorry, I just...

300
00:13:54,890 --> 00:13:57,200
I'm not used to wearing a yukata. It might be too tight.

301
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:57,720
Really?

302
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:00,310
Akari, you should go home for today.

303
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:02,870
Minami-kun isn't coming anyway, right?

304
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:05,570
That's right! Let's start looking for the next chance!

305
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,700
Yeah.

306
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,470
Thanks.

307
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,950
That was a heck of a crowd.

308
00:14:13,950 --> 00:14:16,580
Maybe we should've taken a different street. Sorry.

309
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:21,340
It's okay. The shortest route to the supermarket is through the shrine grounds.

310
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:25,090
Well, my work is that way.

311
00:14:25,090 --> 00:14:27,450
Sorry to make you go shopping all the time.

312
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:30,000
I'll go buy the heavy stuff tomorrow.

313
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,470
Don't worry! Just leave it to me!

314
00:14:32,470 --> 00:14:34,610
We're a married couple, after all.

315
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:37,080
We have to do our best to help each other out!

316
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,980
And this is something that will affect your college references.

317
00:14:40,810 --> 00:14:43,200
You really saved me here. Thanks.

318
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,980
Be careful out there!

319
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:51,780
A fireworks festival...

320
00:14:52,630 --> 00:14:55,180
I wonder if Jiro-kun went...

321
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:03,880
Oh, man.

322
00:15:05,850 --> 00:15:07,510
Did I catch a chill after my bath?

323
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:11,760
And while you're doing that, Minami-kun and I will have a nice mood going.

324
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:16,010
I wonder if Akari's got a nice mood going right now.

325
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:19,270
What'd she mean by a "nice mood," anyway?

326
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:22,110
Like... a kiss?

327
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:29,610
Holding hands, hugging, kissing...

328
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:33,910
They're the same things, but if Tenjin does them, will it make him her boyfriend?

329
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,550
What about me, then?

330
00:15:35,550 --> 00:15:38,540
If we change our pairings and I'm not her mock husband anymore,

331
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,580
then I'll be...

332
00:15:40,130 --> 00:15:41,300
...a friend?

333
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:44,210
No. Just a classmate?

334
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,890
We've spent every day together for so long now,

335
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:49,880
but with the "married couple" aspect gone...

336
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:52,880
Will there really be nothing left?

337
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:58,010
I did all that stuff with her before Tenjin, though...

338
00:16:00,430 --> 00:16:02,990
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Just who do I think I am?!

339
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:04,620
I make myself sick!

340
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:09,530
Tch. Who's calling me now, when I'm feeling this gross?

341
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:15,280
Watanabe Akari Cell Phone

342
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:11,160
Huh?

343
00:16:12,020 --> 00:16:14,570
I can answer, right? I mean, she's the one calling me.

344
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:17,520
Hello?

345
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:19,930
Hello, Akari?

346
00:16:25,010 --> 00:16:26,020
Jiro...

347
00:16:27,410 --> 00:16:28,460
What's wrong?

348
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:30,140
I knew I wasn't...

349
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,430
Where are you right now?

350
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,440
Where are you? I'll be right there.

351
00:16:44,970 --> 00:16:47,690
Jiro... I'm sorry.

352
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:51,440
Jiro!

353
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:54,200
Oh, for crying out loud... I'll run!

354
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:56,740
Tell me where you are!

355
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:59,450
What? Why'd she hang up?!

356
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:02,450
Wait, wait, wait! Hang on a minute! Come on!

357
00:17:02,450 --> 00:17:03,000
All Missed Call Log Watanabe Akari Watanabe Akari Home Watanabe Akari Kamo Home

358
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,210
Watanabe Akari Calling

359
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,830
Come on, answer!

360
00:17:10,850 --> 00:17:11,650
Huh?

361
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:16,840
Akari...

362
00:17:17,930 --> 00:17:21,350
I'm sorry. I ended up coming home.

363
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:26,290
After you did my yukata and everything...

364
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,440
I'm so sorry!

365
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:35,610
Everyone worked so hard for me, but...

366
00:17:36,940 --> 00:17:38,010
I'm sorry.

367
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:39,020
Everyone...

368
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,870
I'm sorry!

369
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,100
Welcome home.

370
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,500
Welcome home, Akari.

371
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:13,320
I'm back, Jiro!

372
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:32,020
Sachi and Natsumi both told me this yukata looked nice on me.

373
00:18:32,020 --> 00:18:33,820
I'm glad I wore it.

374
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:36,140
But doesn't the obi make it hard to breathe?

375
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:38,050
You're home now. Why not take it off?

376
00:18:38,050 --> 00:18:40,640
That's sexual harassment. Gross.

377
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:43,050
That is not what I meant!

378
00:18:44,370 --> 00:18:46,960
Hey, do I look cute in a yukata?

379
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:50,700
What do you think of the wife you dressed yourself?

380
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:56,000
I still think the ribbon bow would suit you better.

381
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Aw, hiding your embarrassment again?

382
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,450
Are you still pouting?

383
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:01,320
You are jealous, aren't you?

384
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:04,330
I don't know.

385
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,980
Whoa, what is it?

386
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:18,090
Give me your hand.

387
00:19:18,350 --> 00:19:19,080
Wait...

388
00:19:19,570 --> 00:19:21,190
What? Huh?

389
00:19:22,490 --> 00:19:23,200
Um... Go ahead.

390
00:19:23,850 --> 00:19:25,660
W-With what?

391
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:27,350
Go ahead and do a ribbon bow.

392
00:19:29,620 --> 00:19:31,390
Do what you like.

393
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:38,220
O-Okay, then...

394
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,030
Aren't you done yet?

395
00:19:50,030 --> 00:19:52,870
The fireworks are gonna be over, clumsy.

396
00:19:52,870 --> 00:19:56,880
No one asked you! This is only the second time in my life I've done this.

397
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:08,410
Uh-oh.

398
00:20:08,410 --> 00:20:10,770
What? Did you mess it up?

399
00:20:10,770 --> 00:20:11,700
No, just...

400
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:14,770
No matter how many times I look at what I'm supposed to do next, I don't get it.

401
00:20:14,770 --> 00:20:16,730
Well, there's a video version, too.

402
00:20:16,730 --> 00:20:17,610
Let me see.

403
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,440
That was close!

404
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,160
Th-This is... It's not...

405
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:32,400
Huh?

406
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,790
H-Hey, let—

407
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:37,790
Hey, Jiro...

408
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,540
Stay like this and say my name.

409
00:20:41,820 --> 00:20:43,890
If you say my name,

410
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:46,300
I feel like I'll be able to try again.

411
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:52,660
Sometimes I lose confidence in myself, you know?

412
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:56,940
Akari.

413
00:20:58,330 --> 00:21:00,690
Yeah. More.

414
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:02,890
Akari.

415
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:04,360
More.

416
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:05,940
Akari.

417
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:15,470
Wow, it's beautiful! And so cute!

418
00:21:15,470 --> 00:21:18,960
Wow, that's amazing! Wait, what is it? A peach?

419
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,910
It's a heart, you dork!

420
00:21:20,910 --> 00:21:22,430
It's upside-down.

421
00:21:22,430 --> 00:21:25,220
Oh... Oh!

422
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:27,040
Jiro...

423
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:29,620
Thanks.

424
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:32,470
For not asking me what happened today.

425
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:37,230
We're married. Helping each other out is what we're supposed to do.

426
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:40,860
I didn't ask because I didn't want to know.

427
00:21:42,180 --> 00:21:45,600
I'm rooting for her to be with Tenjin, but...

428
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,240
Oh, it's upside-down again.

429
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:49,730
When I heard her crying through the phone...

430
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,240
When I realized that she'd come home...

431
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:54,860
Why did I feel relieved?

432
00:21:55,790 --> 00:21:58,470
The timing didn't work out this time,

433
00:21:58,470 --> 00:22:01,830
but there'll be more fireworks festivals this year and next year.

434
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:04,260
Yeah. Thanks.

435
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:06,110
We're a married couple,

436
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:08,680
and marriage means pledging to spend a lifetime together.

437
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,990
But for us, there is no "next year,"

438
00:22:10,990 --> 00:22:13,040
so this small view we see from this veranda...

439
00:22:13,570 --> 00:22:17,710
is probably the first and last fireworks show we'll watch together.

440
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

441
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

442
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

443
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

444
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,480
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

445
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

446
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

447
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

448
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,160
I want to know where my heart is hiding

449
00:22:57,160 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

450
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

451
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

452
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,510
Turn them inside out

453
00:23:08,510 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

454
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

455
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

456
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

457
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

458
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

459
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

460
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:53,260
Actually, I had a yukata all prepared, too.

461
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:55,060
That works surprisingly well!

462
00:23:55,060 --> 00:23:56,760
You didn't need to say "surprisingly"!

463
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:58,330
It's nice! Super nice!

464
00:23:58,330 --> 00:24:00,440
Too bad, though. We're all done here!

465
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,580
Um, actually, I had one ready, too!

466
00:24:04,330 --> 00:24:06,590
Brava! Brava! It's just too good!

467
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:10,090
Next Time An Entreaty, but No Reassurance. Next time, "An Entreaty, but No Reassurance."

